==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chirology
<hw>Chi*rol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chei`r</grk> hand + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The art or
practice of using the manual alphabet or of communicating thoughts by
sings made by the hands and fingers; a substitute for spoken or written
language in intercourse with the deaf and dumb. See
<er>Dactylalogy</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

